        "content": "<p>In <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/22533\">#22533</a> I have some instances of <code>induction</code> where one or more of the initial cases are presented on the same line as the induction.</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">induction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">zero</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"o\">[</span><span class=\"n\">geomSum</span><span class=\"o\">]</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">succ</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ih</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>It is legal syntax, but is this style an acceptable variant?</p>\n<p>(<span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"214703\">@Yury G. Kudryashov</span>, <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/22533#discussion_r1997766857\">https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/22533#discussion_r1997766857</a>)</p>",
        "id": 506012479,
        "sender_full_name": "Jeremy Tan",
        "timestamp": 1742168771
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Note: Jeremy uses this syntax to replace something like</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">induction'</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">n</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">ih</span><span class=\"bp\">;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">·</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">simp</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 506012581,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1742168869
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm not sure I like having multiple cases on the same line like this, but that's style that's up for debate.</p>\n<p>More importantly, I think in the future</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Lean4\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"n\">induction</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">x</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"k\">with</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">|</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">label</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">a</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">b</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">c</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"bp\">=&gt;</span>\n<span class=\"n\">tac1</span>\n<span class=\"n\">tac2</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>will be an error if there's no indentation. This would be to support empty tactic blocks, without giving strange behavior. I don't know for certain yet.</p>\n<p>Two future-proof options: (1) indent, or (2) use <code>induction x with | label a b c =&gt; ?_</code> if you don't want to indent the following lines.</p>",
        "id": 506013193,
        "sender_full_name": "Kyle Miller",
        "timestamp": 1742169452
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I might have been the one introducing the weird <code>induction' ...; · simp</code> syntax when I was cleaning up mathlib for adopting the multiGoal linter.</p>",
        "id": 506075107,
        "sender_full_name": "Damiano Testa",
        "timestamp": 1742199848
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>My personal preference would be to indent, though.</p>",
